        "content": "Here’s what I did to execute process J09C and what the status is:\n\n1. Retrieved the process definition for `process_rule_id = 'J09C'` and confirmed the required steps (creating `J09C_temp`, adding `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, applying rules, joining with `EABLG`, `NET_MASTER`, `SALES_MASTER`, exporting CSV, emailing EVU team, then deleting the temp table).\n\n2. Attempted to access the database:\n   - Called `get_db_schema` to inspect tables.\n   - Ran a test query on `decision_table`:\n     - `SELECT * FROM decision_table LIMIT 1`\n\n3. Both operations failed with the same error:\n   - `\"Error no database connection\"`\n\n   This means:\n   - I cannot read from `decision_table`.\n   - I cannot create the `J09C_temp` table.\n   - I cannot join with `EABLG`, `NET_MASTER`, or `SALES_MASTER`.\n   - I cannot generate the required CSV for J09C.\n\n4. Because this is a system-level database connectivity problem, I escalated it as required:\n   - Sent an email to `support@company.com` via the tooling, with:\n     - Description of the process (`J09C`)\n     - Exact tools called and error messages\n     - Impact on the process (which steps cannot be completed)\n   - The email metadata was stored successfully, indicating the escalation request went through.\n\nCurrent status:\n\n- Process J09C is **blocked** at the very beginning due to lack of database connection.\n- Steps 1–9 of the process cannot be completed until the SQLite connection is restored.\n- Support has been notified; once the database is available again, the process should be re-run from step 1 (creation of `J09C_temp`).\n\nIf you’d like, I can outline the exact SQL I will run for each step once the database is back online, so you have a ready-made runbook.",
